results.name: Maximum rectangle of partitions in Mathematica order.
link: Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, Ferrers Diagram.
example: Partition 34 in Mathematica order is [4,3]; its maximum rectangle is 2x3 = 6, so a(34)=6.
results.author: _Franklin T. Adams-Watters_, Mar 11 2006
